</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is closely related and somewhat similar to both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kostylev" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1012,1186,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pseudepipona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kozhevnikovi">
<emphasis box="[1012,1186,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">P. kozhevnikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kokujev" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1242,1392,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pseudepipona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricarinata">
<emphasis box="[1242,1392,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">P. tricarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from them by a longer clypeus and a longer T 
<quantity box="[899,938,511,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
both the female and the male as well as by a different structure of the genitalia in the male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,456,582,609]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,582,608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
